                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.48 FAA/12–3047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Italy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-30T19:00:00-05:00">December 30, 1947—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2735. <gloss target="#t_Mefa1">Mefa</gloss> 3. Subject: Additional publicity
                    Interim Aid.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Enabling legislation interim aid is Public Law 389 of Dec. 17 entitled
                        “Foreign Aid Act of 1947”.<note n="1" xml:id="d464fn1">61 Stat. 934.</note>
                        Appropriation legislation is Public Law 393 of Dec. 23 entitled “Third
                        Supplemental Appropriation Act, 1948” for fiscal year ending June 30,
                            1948.<note n="2" xml:id="d464fn2">61 Stat. 941.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Use words “United States Foreign Aid Program” as official designation.
                        Abbreviation is <gloss target="#t_USFAP1">USFAP</gloss>, but please use
                            <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 389 in addition in cables to clearly
                        distinguish from <gloss target="#t_USFRP1">USFRP</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 84.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Following is initial portion supply program for Italy approved by Dept
                        under <gloss target="#t_USFAP1">USFAP</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 389. Procurement will be initiated on signature
                        agreement.</item>
                </list>
